## 1. Definitions

### 1.1 "Software"
means the DTQEM source code v46.0, all accompanying files, examples, documentation, and specifically the **core equation (D0)** as applied to the Mach-Zehnder interferometer:

\[
V_{\text{eff}} = \exp(-\gamma_\phi \cdot T_{\text{eff}}) \times \exp\left(-\frac{|\Delta\tau|}{\tau_c}\right)
\]

where:
- \(T_{\text{eff}} = \frac{\tau_1 + \tau_2}{2}\) (effective environmental interaction time)
- \(\Delta\tau = \left| \frac{L_1}{v_1 \gamma_1} - \frac{L_2}{v_2 \gamma_2} \right|\) (proper-time mismatch)
- \(\tau_i = L_i / v_i\) (lab-frame transit time)
- \(\gamma_i = 1 / \sqrt{1 - v_i^2/c^2}\) (Lorentz factor)
- \(\tau_c\) – the only free parameter (proper-time coherence constant)

The Software includes the following code modules (v46.0 and v44.0):

| # | File | Version | Description |
|---|------|---------|-------------|
| 1 | `dtqem_mach_zehnder_v46.py` | v46.0 | Mach-Zehnder interferometer (stable) |
| 2 | `dtqem_double_slit_forward_v44.py` | v44.0 | Double-slit forward model |
| 3 | `dtqem_double_slit_inverse_v44.py` | v44.0 | Double-slit inverse model |
| 4 | `dtqem_qubit_decoherence_v44.py` | v44.0 | Qubit decoherence simulator |
| 5 | `dtqem_zeeman_effect_v44.py` | v44.0 | Zeeman effect simulator |
| 6 | `dtqem_wave_code_v44.py` | v44.0 | Core wave functions |
| 7 | `c70_benchmark.py` | experimental | Benchmark against C70 data |
| 8 | `dtqem_mass_effect_demo_v3.py` | experimental | Mass-dependent τ_c demo (P9) |

All derivatives of these equations, whether in source or object form, and the accompanying code, test scripts, examples, and documentation are covered by this license.

